# API — {{API_FRAMEWORK}} REST Routes

## ROUTE STRUCTURE
- Routes live in `{{API_DIR}}/`
- Pattern: {{ROUTE_PATTERN}}
<!-- ROUTE_PATTERN example: "app/api/[resource]/route.ts for Next.js App Router" -->
- DO: One file per resource — group CRUD handlers together

## REQUEST VALIDATION
- ALWAYS validate with {{VALIDATION_LIBRARY}} before processing
- Schema files live in `{{SCHEMAS_DIR}}/` (or colocated — match existing pattern)
- Return 400 with structured error on validation failure:
```
{ error: "Validation failed", details: [...] }
```

## RESPONSE FORMAT
- Success: `{{ '{' }} data: T, meta?: {...} {{ '}' }}`
- Error: `{{ '{' }} error: string, code?: string {{ '}' }}`
- Use {{HTTP_STATUS_PATTERN}} status codes — no 200 for errors

## AUTH
- Auth middleware: {{AUTH_MIDDLEWARE}}
- Protect routes via: {{AUTH_PATTERN}}
<!-- AUTH_PATTERN example: "export const middleware = withAuth(handler)" -->
- NEVER trust client-supplied user IDs — read from session/JWT

## ERROR HANDLING
- Pattern: {{ERROR_PATTERN}}
<!-- ERROR_PATTERN example: "try/catch with centralized error handler; log with structured logger" -->
- NEVER expose stack traces or internal errors to clients
- Log errors with: `{{LOGGER}}.error({ err, route, userId })`

## AFTER EVERY CHANGE
Run: `{{CMD_TYPECHECK}}` then `{{CMD_TEST}} {{TEST_FILTER_FLAG}} api`
